ECR access for {{ ansible_hostname }}
===============================

Your private ECR repository (Paris region):
- Repository URL: {{ student_ecr.repository_url }}
- Registry host : {{ student_ecr.registry_host }}
- Region        : {{ student_ecr.region | default('eu-west-3') }}

Docker auth is automatic through docker credential helper (profile `ecr`).
No manual docker login command is required.

Build/tag/push examples:
  docker build -t {{ student_ecr.repository_name }}:front-v1 ./frontend
  docker tag {{ student_ecr.repository_name }}:front-v1 {{ student_ecr.repository_url }}:front-v1
  docker push {{ student_ecr.repository_url }}:front-v1

In Kubernetes manifests on EKS, use images like:
  {{ student_ecr.repository_url }}:front-v1

Useful command to parse only the ECR repository name from this file:
  awk -F': ' '/^- Repository URL:/ {print $2}' ~/.kube/ecr_access_info.txt | awk -F'/' '{print $NF}'

